      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically robust example of the legendary S54-powered platform. The 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six features individual throttle bodies and a high-revving valvetrain that remains crisp following a recent shim-and-bucket valve adjustment. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and professional reinforcement of the rear subframe mounting points to ensure chassis rigidity. Power is managed through a tactile 6-speed manual transmission and delivered via a factory limited-slip differential. The suspension retains its signature handling characteristics with refreshed bushings and dampers. While the car shows minor cosmetic evidence of spirited use, the drivetrain and structural integrity are excellent, offering the visceral, high-compression performance purists demand.",
